esus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 14, \"to\": 22}, {\"ngram\": \"Opinion\", \"from\": 23, \"to\": 30}, {\"ngram\": \"Peacock\", \"from\": 31, \"to\": 38}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports\", \"from\": 39, \"to\": 45}, {\"ngram\": \"TV\", \"from\": 46, \"to\": 48}, {\"ngram\": \"TV| Tagged\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 59}, {\"ngram\": \"olympics\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 72}, {\"ngram\": \"opinion\", \"from\": 73, \"to\": 80}, {\"ngram\": \"paris\", \"from\": 81, \"to\": 86}, {\"ngram\": \"peacock\", \"from\": 87, \"to\": 94}, {\"ngram\": \"a controversial moment\", \"from\": 152, \"to\": 174}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Personally, the 2024 Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony was everything we were hoping it would be and more.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A wee bit long?\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure!\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 361, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But how can you argue withLady Gaga,Celine Dion, and some amazingly wonderful visuals that embraced the host city's culture, history, and artistry?\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.254500429026386e-20, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 398, \"end\": 409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.514473308191947e-29, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some amazingly wonderful visuals\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"the host city's culture\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 485}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 494}, {\"ngram\": \"artistry\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well\\u2026 apparently, a lot of folks are taking issue with one segment of the ceremony, in particular - but it turns out that they might be barking up the wrong crucifix.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 676, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"folks\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"issue\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 559}, {\"ngram\": \"one segment\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 576}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 592}, {\"ngram\": \"the wrong crucifix\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Set on a footbridge across the Seine, DJ, producer, and LGBTQ+ activistBarbara Butchwas surrounded by other drag artists, performers, and dancers, creating a scene that many saw as a take onLeonardo da Vinci's \\\"Last Supper\\\" (depicting Jesus Christ's final time with his main followers where he would reveal that one of his apostles would betray him\\u2026 and you know how things went from there).\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 708, \"end\": 713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999706628846, \"rank\": 2.173535261462727e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9984875994385077, \"rank\": 0.0015146913812093248, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a footbridge\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"DJ\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"producer\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"LGBTQ+ activistBarbara\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"Butchwas\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"other drag artists\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 797}, {\"ngram\": \"performers\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"dancers\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 822}, {\"ngram\": \"a scene\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"a take onLeonardo da Vinci's \\\"Last Supper\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"his main followers\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"his apostles\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can only imagine what the Christian community thought about the moment - actually, you do not have to imagine because it did not take long for a lot of folks (like Republican Speaker of the HouseMike Johnson- a supporter ofDonald Trump) to lash out at the ceremony as being a mockery of Christianity.\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9981494820873628, \"rank\": 0.0018539485277861783, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999290348862153, \"rank\": 6.30384378089621e-05, \"text\": \"Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999838023542, \"rank\": 1.6197215121558666e-08, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"folks\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"the HouseMike Johnson-\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"a supporter\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1337}, {\"ngram\": \"a mockery\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1356}, {\"ngram\": \"Christianity\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1372}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Except\\u2026 it looks like they may have gotten it wrong.\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1426, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking with French news channel BFM-TV on Sunday and reported on by NBC's Today,Thomas Jolly, the opening ceremony's artistic director, defended the moment by explaining that the inspiration had nothing to do with Da Vinci and Jesus and everything to do with the Dionysus (aka Bacchus), the Greek God of wine-making, orchards and fruit, vegetation, fertility, festivity, insanity, ritual madness, religious ecstasy, and theatre (thank you, Wikipedia - would have missed a few of those).\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1442, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9998346541406775, \"rank\": 0.00016481477120526412, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1498, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999909799978274, \"rank\": 7.794137559151107e-06, \"text\": \"